text: Lawmakers must turn away from the gun lobby and heed the pleas of inspiring students demanding change.
We must strengthen our background check system to prevent guns from falling into the wrong hands. My #FixNICS bill w/ @ChrisMurphyCT would do just that – and Congress should pass it.

I'll fight for real reforms – inspired by the energy and courage of students who have marched in the street – including banning assault weapons, limiting high-capacity magazines, and universal background checks.
Arming teachers, militarizing schools, and sending our children into classrooms wearing bulletproof backpacks is no answer to gun violence.
It is disgraceful that Republicans seem more willing to turn schools into free-fire zones than to make even a single concession to the NRA.
Pres. Trump and the NRA's attempt to blame a mass shooting on anything but the weapon of war used to commit it would be pathetic if it weren’t so dangerous.
The @FCC’s misguided move to dismantle #NetNeutrality – handing over our free & open internet to profit-hungry corporations - will be met with fierce outrage and outcry in every corner of America.
Now that Pres. Trump has listened, he must act. Push Congress to pass stronger background checks and bans on high-capacity magazines and bump stocks. No more fatal fealty to NRA.
Inspired by the #Parkland survivors and parents who boldly spoke out at last night’s #CNNTownHall – refuting desperate NRA deflections and refusing to temper calls for reform. Thank you.
Firearms for teachers is toxic lunacy – an NRA-backed distraction from commonsense action. Teachers, principals, police, and school boards oppose it for good reason.
After listening, Pres. Trump needs to lead - and act. Support universal background checks, bans on assault weapons and high-capacity magazines.
Monstrously misguided Concealed Carry Reciprocity bill is DOA in Senate - a demise it richly deserves. It mocks gun violence victims and their loved ones.

Our #FixNICS bill would close information gaps in the background check database - helping keep guns away from dangerous buyers. Bipartisan support, now Trump support, overwhelming popular support - no excuse for continued delay.
Trump words supporting our bipartisan #FixNICS bill must be backed by action. He must throw away the NRA playbook and break the gun lobby’s grip. Students showing the way.

Blockbuster indictment of Russian agents should stop Trump rants and sycophants’ chants aimed at Special Counsel. Firing Mueller now would be a gift to Putin, a boon to Russia, and a threat to America.
We don’t have higher mental illness rates in America, Mr. President – but we do have easier access to weapons of war. A ban on assault weapons won't stop every tragedy, but it will save lives.
Sympathies from Pres. Trump are important but insufficient. More than words, action needed now to confront gun violence and prevent future massacres.
Thankful for every American who has spoken out and demanded action to curb gun violence. Your voices of reason are needed now more than ever – and I will continue to amplify them in Washington.
We cannot accept a world where so many of America’s elected representatives put fidelity to the NRA over their constituents’ demands for action on gun violence.
Columbine, Virginia Tech, Sandy Hook – now #Parkland. The list goes on, as does Congress's cowardly complicity. When will my colleagues put children’s lives ahead of the gun lobby's bottom line?
Tragedies like #Parkland are not inevitable and they cannot deter us from demanding action on gun violence. We owe it to victims, loved ones and families to fight harder than ever before.

The list grows - now more than 100 national security ticking time bombs lacking necessary clearance, putting secrets and sources in peril. If they can’t be cleared, fire them - or deny classified access.
My heart breaks as Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School of Parkland, FL faces the unthinkable horror of gun violence – the 18th school shooting of 2018. When will Congress wake up? Enough is enough.

Closely following reports of a school shooting in Parkland, Florida – my thoughts are with the victims, loved ones, and all affected. Thankful for the swift action of courageous first responders on scene.
Great countries do not break their promises. Under #DACA, the United States promised #Dreamers protection for coming out of the shadows. We must keep our word now.

Imagine your whole life ripped away from you – your job, your home, your family – because of a choice you didn’t even make. That's the nightmare #Dreamers face right now, and Congress shouldn't tolerate it for another minute.
This week, the Senate can vote to give #Dreamers – Americans in all but name – the future they deserve. Let’s seize the moment and #ProtectDreamers.
Intel Community heads agree Russian meddlers will return – but Pres. Trump continues to deny reality and disregard sanctions Congress passed 517-5. Americans are right to ask: Why?
Stunning and inexplicable that none of the Intel Community heads were consulted on #NunesMemo before White House recklessly released it – putting political vendettas ahead of national security.

White House must disclose to Congress 30 to 40 top-level Presidential staff who still have only interim security clearances - failed to be deemed trustworthy a full year into this Administration - yet given access to classified secret information.
Budgets reflect values. Pres. Trump's budget – brimming with broken promises, monstrous cuts to the social safety net, and wasteful wall spending – couldn't do a better job reflecting his.
More for hedge funds than hard hats, Pres. Trump's #InfrastructurePlan relies on magical thinking, massive private interest profits, and a pittance of public investment.

As a prosecutor, I saw plenty of defense teams try to put the government on trial. Now, the nation sees Trump’s Capitol Hill lackeys using this well-worn tactic against the FBI/DOJ - with bogus memos and public attacks.

Congratulations to Mark Arcobello, Mac Bohonnon, Zachary Donohue, Lindsey Jacobellis, Julia Marino, Kiley McKinnon, Tucker West, and Emily Sweeney – the EIGHT Olympians from the Nutmeg State! So proud to have you representing Connecticut and #TeamUSA in Pyeongchang!

Congress has finally produced a long-term spending deal worthy of the constituents who sent us here– a significant bipartisan achievement that invests in military & non-military spending to support our troops, keep our nation safe, & fulfill our obligations to the American people
This Administration’s fast-and-loose attitude on security clearances goes far deeper than Rob Porter – from Kushner to Flynn, and who knows how many others?

Chilling lapses in security and background clearance process shown by Rob Porter’s access to classified info. White House indifference, on full display at today’s press briefing, should outrage and frighten everyone.

Family and Medical Leave Act protections have given millions of Americans job security and peace of mind. On its 25th anniversary, let’s take the next step and expand #PaidLeave with the #FAMILYAct. #FMLA25
Yesterday's #Amtrak crash was preventable with Positive Train Control, saving lives and dollars. @USDOT must hold railroads’ feet to the fire and ensure they implement PTC by this year's deadline.

The #NunesMemo is a desperate bid by Trump & Republicans to smear the Special Counsel. Trump reportedly said as much by telling associates that the memo will undermine Mueller's probe. Career public servants at the FBI will needlessly suffer from this brazen ploy.
President Trump in that chamber was more a Divider-in-Chief than a unifier. #SOTU
Who will show up for #SOTU tonight, Teleprompter Trump or Twitter Trump? America deserves better than the Divider-in-Chief.

Which other White House officials and aides were involved in discussions around possible Mueller firing, as reported in Thursday’s NY Times and Washington Post stories? America needs to hear the truth from them.
Repugnant Trump immigration plan holds #Dreamers hostage and orders draconian restrictions – while doubling down on wasteful wall funding. A non-starter in the Senate.

Partnering with @JerryMoran to demand @USAGym, @MichiganStateU, and the US Olympic Committee answer for their systemic failure to shield athletes from sexual abuse. The women who bravely exposed Larry Nassar’s criminal conduct deserve nothing less.
Russian meddling didn't end in 2016. Just this month, Russian-linked Twitter accounts bolstered misleading partisan efforts to disrupt the Russia investigation and shut down the federal government.
Candidate Trump talked a big game about fixing America’s #infrastructure. President Trump outrageously was all-talk for over a year – and then his pathetically inadequate plan Monday.
My heart goes out to the victims of this week’s tragedies in Texas and Kentucky – two school shootings in as many days. When will Congress meet this urgent public health crisis with action? #Enough
Today’s stopgap three-week patch shortchanges Connecticut’s needs and kicks the can down the road - for the fourth time in as many months.
Congress must do its job. Serious talks and compromise by the Republican leadership and the President could have avoided this self-inflicted crisis – and still can.
We’ve already waited months for a resolution on #DACA, robust disaster relief, and funds for health programs that millions rely on. Republicans need to end this embarrassing episode and get to work.

Americans see this self-inflicted, senseless dysfunction for what it is – and they know exactly who is at fault. Republicans should listen to their constituents and work to avert a #TrumpShutdown before it’s too late.

We owe this country real action on real problems – not another stopgap CR that ignores #DACA, Community Health Centers, disaster relief, and so much more. Time to negotiate on a bipartisan basis and avert a #TrumpShutdown.
Passing what would be the fourth short-term CR in as many months delays defense programs – we urgently need full year funding for national security, both military and non-military.

Republicans could have taken the bipartisan approach Americans want and deserve. Instead, they’re using kids’ healthcare as a bargaining chip, leaving #Dreamers in limbo, and pushing us toward a #TrumpShutdown. This is what failed leadership looks like.

.@FEMA’s sudden reversal of Transitional Shelter Assistance aid for 45 displaced Puerto Rican families in CT is a shocking betrayal of public trust - rescinding vital housing support for families in the dead of winter without even a full day's notice.

Brian Benczkowski, who represented a large Russian bank with ties to Putin, refuses to recuse himself from the Mueller investigation. His appointment to lead DOJ's powerful Criminal Division would imperil that vital effort.

My heart breaks as Joel Colindres fights yet another cold, callous attempt to break apart his beautiful family. I am in close contact with the Colindres family and their attorney to support all efforts to keep Joel here in #Connecticut where he belongs.
Bannon’s stonewalling based on bogus pretense of executive privilege is unfounded and untenable. Congress should do its job and hold him in contempt.
#MLKDay has never been more important - recommitting to ideals of equality, tolerance and respect. We are measured at moments of adversity and challenge. Stay true to Dr. King’s moral compass.
My Republican colleagues have an obligation to reject the repugnant, racist views underpinning Trump’s immigration priorities. They can start by backing the bipartisan #DACA compromise.
President Trump’s remarks smack of blatant racism – odious and insidious racism masquerading poorly as immigration policy. He does not speak for me as an American.

Abusive employers lure foreign workers to the United States with false promises of jobs - only to coerce them into the sex trade and domestic servitude. Reporting gaps in temporary worker visa programs help traffickers get away with it. Today we say: No more.

Releasing Glenn Simpson's interview w/ Judiciary Committee advances the American people’s right and need to know the full truth. I applaud @SenFeinstein’s leadership in using her proper authority as Ranking Member to serve this public interest.
Heartened to see 114,134 #CT residents sign up for healthcare during last year’s #OpenEnrollment – despite the Trump Administration's ceaseless efforts to sabotage the #ACA.
Less than a month ago – despite massive public outcry – @AjitPaiFCC recklessly repealed the #NetNeutrality rules underpinning our free and open internet. But this battle is nowhere near over.
Fellow Americans in Puerto Rico should be angry - I am furious - at shamefully inadequate federal recovery aid. I will fight for a major Supplemental package, beginning today.
With nuclear war at stake, Trump’s schoolyard taunts and threats against North Korea are dangerous and demeaning. Alas, new year, same Trump.

Great meeting with the Foundation for Puerto Rico, a nonprofit investing in economic development, solar energy, & hurricane relief- & engaging with partners on the mainland. Together with #NH4PR, the Foundation brought 90 mattresses to a PR community in need. More must be done.
Happy New Year, Connecticut! Wishing you and your loved ones a happy, healthy, and safe 2018.

Saddened to hear of the death of Fran Schneidau - a consummate professional whose passion for asking the right questions served @WCBS880 listeners so well for nearly four decades. She will be sorely missed.
Merry Christmas to everyone celebrating in Connecticut and around the world! Wishing you a warm, wonderful holiday surrounded by family and friends.

Last night’s Continuing Resolution left so many national priorities undone:

❌ Protection for #Dreamers
❌ Disaster relief for Puerto Rico, the Gulf, and California
❌ Long-term funding for #CHIP and Community Health Centers
 
That's why I voted NO.

I voted against last night's Continuing Resolution. There's no excuse for Congress's abject failure to meet our most basic obligations. Lurching from crisis to near catastrophe is no way to govern and certainly no way to lead.
This afternoon, I spoke on the Senate Floor to raise the alarm about the looming Constitutional crisis we face – one that threatens the very foundation of our democracy.

We must keep faith with the dedicated #Dreamers who make this great nation even greater - and that means passing the #DreamActNow. I will vote against any Continuing Resolution that fails to include the #DreamAct. #NoDreamNoDeal
Congratulations to Geno and Chris on your 1,000th win - and being teacher and mentor to so many. #Geno1000

A tax bill is a moral statement. This one betrays basic American values. It funds burgeoning tax breaks for the wealthiest one percent – who receive 83 percent of the bill’s benefits – by burdening our children with trillions in debt.
Imagine spending the holidays racked with fear of deportation. That’s the reality for thousands of #Dreamers right now. We cannot wait any longer to pass the #DreamAct.
Unconscionable delays in implementing Positive Train Control now a potential factor in Amtrak tragedy. We cannot afford more delays sought by railroads.
Technology like Positive Train Control must be implemented immediately to prevent trains from speeding and flying off rails. Statutory deadline is 2018 – no excuses.
My heart goes out to the victims, loved ones, and all impacted by today's Amtrak tragedy in Washington State. Grateful for the quick action of first responders on the scene.

Still a massive bait-and-switch, this #GOPTaxScam skewers the middle class and enriches the wealthy and big corporations - creating mountains of debt for our children. I'm fighting it and so should you.
Republicans want to stuff the #GOPTaxScam with permanent corporate favors at working families’ expense. If only they cared this much about re-upping #CHIP health funds for 9 million kids!
The #GOPTaxScam reminds me of a dead fish - the longer it sits out, the more it stinks.
Today’s rollback of #NetNeutrality is a brazen betrayal of American consumers, innovators, students, and entrepreneurs – all of whom will suffer tremendously without a free and open internet.
Today we mark five years since the tragedy at #SandyHook Elementary School in #Newtown - one of the darkest moments in our nation’s history.

Rosenstein stood strong against disgraceful attacks by GOP Congressmen on Mueller inquiry today - a shameful effort to distract and sabotage the investigation with deceptive calls for second Special Counsel.
As we head into the holidays, we cannot forget the thousands of #DREAMers living in chaos and confusion because of Trump’s disgraceful #DACA rescission. They deserve our backing right now.
Congratulations to Doug Jones - a decent man and dedicated U.S. Attorney who will stand up for working families in the Senate. We should listen to what he said last night and fund #CHIP now!
Wishing a joyful and bright #Hanukkah to all who are celebrating in Connecticut and around the world!

Retweet if you agree @AjitPaiFCC should delay Thursday’s #NetNeutrality vote pending a full investigation of possible bot interference in the public comment process. The future of our internet is simply too important.

The people of Connecticut know what a disaster it would be if @AjitPaiFCC succeeds in rolling back #NetNeutrality. I couldn’t agree more! Please keep speaking out and standing up for a level playing field.
I stand with Sen. Gillibrand, a dedicated public servant and friend. America must reject Trump’s sexist slurs.

#NewBritain’s Mariano Cardoso has called America home for 27 years – raising a family, paying taxes, and giving back to his community. Deporting him while his permanent residency application remains pending is simply shameful.

I am optimistic that ongoing, bipartisan talks will pave the way for action to protect 700k DREAMers (incl. about 8k in CT) from unprecedented, unwise deportation. Time to give these talented, hardworking young people the permanent solution they deserve. #HereToStay
Deeply disappointed by House passage of the Concealed Carry Reciprocity Act – an appalling bill that will hamper gun safety measures and endanger law enforcement in states like Connecticut.

The Concealed Carry Reciprocity Act would force Connecticut to recognize concealed carry permits from states with much looser or even nonexistent standards – weakening law enforcement and public safety. We must #StopCCR.
Pres. Trump’s action in Utah sets a dangerous precedent that threatens environmental treasures everywhere. We must protect our natural heritage for future generations. #MonumentsForAll
Trump's claim today that he fired Flynn because of lies to FBI, as well as Pence, shows knowledge of lawbreaking he concealed - never before disclosed.

Americans will remember this day - and the Senate Republican majority will rue it - for the catastrophic scam foisted on the American people in the dead of night. It is a bait-and-switch, promising a simpler and fairer tax code, and actually making it more complex and unfair.
With the #GOPTaxScam, the wealthiest get tax cuts they don’t need, while everyday people get higher premiums they can’t afford. A stark reminder of who Republicans really work for.
The Special Counsel's investigation has breached the White House gates, reaching one of Pres. Trump's most trusted confidants and unmistakably implicating other top officials.
Republicans just postponed the #GOPTaxScam vote until tomorrow. We cannot let up now! Please keep raising your voices against this unconscionable bill.
Today, every last Republican on the Senate Budget Committee voted (with no debate) to advance huge giveaways for the wealthiest and stick everyday Americans with the tab.
Proud to join my colleagues in announcing a long-term, comprehensive plan to help fellow Americans in Puerto Rico & U.S. Virgin Islands recover and rebuild.
#DREAMers in Connecticut and across America deserve peace of mind - not betrayal. RT if you agree: We must #ProtectDREAMers and pass the #DREAMAct by year’s end.
Heading back to DC and ready to fight tooth and nail against the malicious and misguided #GOPTaxPlan – which could get a vote as soon as this week.
From our family to yours, Happy #Thanksgiving! Wishing you a wonderful holiday surrounded by family and friends.
Uber put its customers and employees at serious risk by not only failing to notify the public of the data breach but by taking affirmative steps to bury the news and paying off the hackers.
Every year in America, hundreds of thousands of kids are treated in hospitals for preventable toy-related injuries. Parental vigilance can often make a world of difference.
Department of Justice suit blocking AT&T/Time Warner merger is highly significant as an apparent effort to protect competition and consumers.
This morning, fellow Americans in #PuertoRico and #USVI awoke to their third month without power or access to basic necessities.

Informative conversation this afternoon w/ @HispanicFedCT and @PeaceCenterofCT on steps we can take to end #GunViolence in #CT and nationwide. Grateful for all who joined and asked such thoughtful questions.

The @HouseGOP tax bill is a classic bait-and-switch - and the proof will be in middle class Americans' paychecks, where many will see higher taxes. This giveaway to the wealthiest should be dead on arrival in the Senate.
Powerful alliance across the aisle could be a step toward more effective measures against gun violence.
Americans have waited long enough for commonsense reforms to curb gun violence. Today, we are taking bipartisan action.
Hoping for announcement soon on bipartisan gun violence legislation.

Yesterday we learned there were 130 reported hate crimes on the basis of gender identity in 2016 – up 10% from 2015. This Transgender Awareness Week, I urge my colleagues to support the NO HATE Act & redouble the fight against hate & violence in all forms. #TransWeek
Office pool question: How many times will AG Sessions say “I can’t answer that” during this hearing?
Unresponsive and unaccountable. AG Sessions repeatedly refuses to answer, invoking bogus executive privilege.

America's teachers make tremendous sacrifices to support their students – often spending hundreds out of their own pockets on supplies every year. The last thing we should do is nix their tax break to offset more giveaways to billionaires.
Thanks to the vets at Charles W Wood VFW Post 10321 for inviting me to join your #VeteransDay celebration w/Mayor Leng&State Senator Logan
Stood w/ @MayorHarp and the @cityofnewhaven today to thank the brave men&women who have served or are now serving now around the globe
President Trump shld put American nat’l security first instead of being solicitous of a KGB thug who attacked our democracy&elections.
Russia bullying American media like CNN endangers press freedoms everywhere—encouraging other threats.
Pres Trump’s dangerous denial of Russian meddling in 2016 undermines U.S. intelligence community&threatens security of future elections
#VeteransDay reminds us of our obligation to keep faith w/ all who have served. We are a stronger nation because of your selfless sacrifice.
On #VeteransDay we honor the men and women who have worn the uniform of our great country – and the families who have sacrificed with them.
Today we express our unending gratitude to all whose service to our nation has helped make it the greatest on Earth. #VeteransDay
By giving the wealthiest a tax write-off while slashing benefits for the vulnerable&middle class, GOP tax bill betrays American values.
Republican tax plan is a betrayal of the goal of tax reform: simplicity&fairness.
GOP is celebrating #VeteransDay by eviscerating tax credit that supports hiring our nation's heroes.
Proud to stand w/ @RepJohnLarson @RepJoeCourtney @RepEsty @rosadelauro today speaking out against cruel GOP tax proposal.
As we recognize the service&sacrifice of all who’ve served, we must keep our promise to Puerto Rico’s vets through action&commit to support full recovery on the island
As we pause today to recognize the service&sacrifice of those who have dedicated their lives to defending our country, the crew of the Rose must never be forgotten.
True tax reform shld help all Americans get ahead-Republicans shld commit to responsible, transparent&bipartisan process to reach that goal
America is fed up with malicious and misguided policies that target middle class families.
Tax plan is fundamentally unfair&fiscally irresponsible-a massive tax cut for the wealthy that leaves the rest of America holding the bag
Gutting #SALT deduction will devastate families who save thousands each year&communities that benefit from the support for local services.
Completely eliminating the state&local tax deduction is a partisan ploy to punish states like Connecticut.
The millions of Americans who saw false&inflammatory posts generated by foreign agents here on @Twitter should know how they were exposed to Russian propaganda.
Manufacturers issue recalls. Newspapers print corrections. Social media giants should notify users how they’ve been exposed to Russian lies on their platforms.
The Stop Enabling Sex Traffickers Act - bipartisan legislation I sponsored with @SenRobPortman - was approved by the Senate Commerce Committee this morning.
Connecticut knows the horror of gun violence all too well. We grieve with the brave souls in Texas enduring unspeakable pain.
Why wasn't TX killer's domestic violence conviction reported by Air Force? DoD must provide answers. For law to work, all must participate.
My bipartisan legislation with @SenRobPortman to combat sex trafficking is set to be considered by the Commerce Committee this Wednesday.
Sec. Ross’s stake in company so closely tied to Putin inner circle raises profound question: Can he put America's interests before his own?
Heartbroken for victims, loved ones, and all affected by the horrific tragedy in Sutherland Springs, Texas.
In light of this week's news, AG Sessions needs to explain what he really knew about Trump campaign communications with Russia. Now.
For America’s middle class, this monstrously regressive Republican tax plan gives “mean” new meaning.
My heart is with all affected by the tragedy in Manhattan. Grateful for the efforts of brave first responders and law enforcement on scene.
Message from Special Counsel to lawbreakers: Cooperate now (Papadopoulos) or risk indictment (Manafort).
We now know Trump's campaign was run by an accused Russian foreign agent charged w/ conspiring against US & laundering payments from Moscow.
Conspiracy indictment is a chilling story of blatant lawbreaking - need to know which others involved.
Deeply humbled to receive @NewtownAction "Honor With Action" award along w/ my colleagues. Together we can curb gun violence and save lives.
GOP #TaxPlan is a middle class sucker-punch - jacking up taxes on 428K Connecticut households to pay for giveaways to the wealthy.
CT families suffering from the opioid crisis deserve better than half-measures and empty rhetoric offered seemingly as an afterthought.
Proud to join my colleague @ChrisMurphyCT on the Background Check Expansion Act - a commonsense reform to keep guns out of the wrong hands.
Last night, @SenateGOP and VP Pence voted to take power from you and hand it to corporations like Wells Fargo and Equifax.
No excuse for denying a young woman’s right to make her own reproductive choices. Period. #JusticeForJane
Puerto Ricans are patriotic Americans who have fought in our wars for generations. They deserve better than our failing federal response.
Reminder: CHIP health funds for 9M kids (inc. 17K in CT) expired 23 days ago. Instead of fixing, @SenateGOP is focused on tax cuts for rich.
I’m voting for short term relief package tomorrow, but working on longer, larger recovery measure with real investment for PR's future.
Trump deserves a 10 for Puerto Rico performance. But only if the scale is 1 to 100, usual for grading. Mr. President, do better today.
This year ICE agents have violated @DHSgov policy by detaining immigrants at sensitive locations like hospitals, churches, even schools.
Reminder: Two weeks ago, the Trump Admin gave businesses free rein to interfere in their employees' reproductive healthcare choices.
Budget resolution is straight from Trump playbook: Guts Medicare/Medicaid, abandons infrastructure, & shifts tax burden to working families.
This bipartisan healthcare agreement is a victory for American patients & consumers, showing how we can work together across party lines.
Nearly a month after Maria, Puerto Rico is teetering toward a terrifying collapse with deadly consequences. We cannot turn a blind eye.
A robust, free press is the cornerstone of our democracy – ensuring public access to news without government meddling or censorship.
ACA is law of the land. President Trump should work w/ both parties on improvements, instead of using regular Americans as political pawns.
Americans need to know whether the Trump Administration is truly focused on helping millions of citizens suffering in Puerto Rico.
Trump's sabotage of ACA seems boundless - a health care tragedy unfolding for countless Americans.
Failure to certify Iran Agreement today undermines America’s credibility with allies and jeopardizes ability to hold Iran accountable.
Humanitarian crisis, calamity & chaos in Puerto Rico are why I'm demanding a disaster relief czar - to cut through red tape & deliver help.
The #CleanPowerPlan was a bold step toward curbing carbon emissions, promoting public health, and embracing a clean energy future.
Trump admin’s list of immigration demands is a slap in the face to DREAMers and an affront to the values that make America great.
Gutting ACA contraception mandate is another backward step by an Admin apparently unconcerned w/ women's financial & physical well-being.
The NRA call for review & regulation of bump stocks is a dangerous, deceptive dodge. Bump stocks should be banned completely - right now.
Unlike virtually all other goods manufacturers, the gun industry cannot be sued by consumers harmed by their products. That is outrageous.
Pleased that @SenateCommerce included my bill with @SenatorWicker to curb child hot car deaths in #AVSTART legislative package.
Proud to join @SenFeinstein & many others on bill to ban sale of bump stocks - carnage force multipliers that have no place in our society.
I thank everyone who has spoken up for commonsense gun violence prevention measures. Your voices of reason are more vital than ever.
We have it in our power to curb gun violence and save lives. It is that simple. Congress is complicit each day it fails to act.
Questioned Secretary Mattis today on the urgent need for a greater @DeptofDefense role in Puerto Rico relief efforts.
My heart breaks with sorrow for Las Vegas, but my stomach churns with anger. I am furious.
My heart breaks for Las Vegas - prayers to families and loved ones. The nation's conscience must be galvanized.
Double standard for disaster relief is unacceptable. Our fellow Americans in Puerto Rico deserve more and better aid.
Heading to @FEMA HQ in DC tomorrow to question top FEMA & administration officials on recovery efforts in Puerto Rico & US Virgin Islands.
Allowing health center & Children's Health Insurance Program funding to lapse is political malpractice to the point of purposeful neglect.
This afternoon I spoke on the Senate Floor for the third time in as many days about a humanitarian crisis affecting millions of Americans.
To our fellow citizens in Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands: You are not alone in this humanitarian crisis. Congress will have your back.
This is a make-or-break moment. #GrahamCassidy's fate will hinge on which side fights hardest this week. Don't let up now.
We are better than a bill that cuts coverage for millions, slashes Medicaid, and weakens women's health. We are better than #GrahamCassidy.
Make no mistake: #GrahamCassidy is 100% rotten to the core. Desperate, last-minute giveaways cannot change that.
I am concerned by reports of carbon monoxide deaths & poisonings resulting from portable generators used after recent natural disasters.
The heartbreaking humanitarian crisis facing Puerto Rico after #HurricaneMaria demands more than sympathy and well-wishes. We must act now.
Sen. McCain’s characteristic courage and conviction in rejecting #GrahamCassidy should inspire my colleagues to take a bipartisan approach.
This administration’s stunning insensitivity and indifference to the pervasive problem of campus sexual assault reached a new low today.
Memo to my GOP colleagues: We weren't elected to curtail coverage for millions of our fellow Americans.
#GrahamCassidy would restrict Medicaid patients from accessing vital care - incl. cancer screenings - at Planned Parenthood health centers.
Republicans should dump #GrahamCassidy and embrace bipartisanship. If they refuse, we'll fight back every step of the way.
Americans deserve bipartisan healthcare fixes, not a slap in the face. #GrahamCassidy shouldn't get one vote, let alone a majority.
The GOP's plot to ram #GrahamCassidy through without a CBO score or regular order tells you everything you need to know about it.
Today I'm criss-crossing Connecticut to talk with patients, providers, and advocates about the disastrous #GrahamCassidy healthcare bill.
This is it! Senate Finance Committee needs to hear from you before Monday’s #GrahamCassidy hearing. Email gchcomments@finance.senate.gov
Flame retardant chemicals found in products like mattresses can release toxic fumes during fires - endangering families and firefighters.
#GrahamCassidy is the king of mean. It dwarfs anything we have seen in terms of its cruelty to the American people.
My thoughts are with everyone in Puerto Rico facing down #HurricaneMaria, the second storm to affect the island in as many weeks.
I am horrified that once again, we must fight back against a healthcare bill that would devastate health & finances of countless families.
Proud to have testified in favor of #SESTA at Commerce Committee today. Online sex trafficking survivors deserve their day in court.
Happy birthday to the @USAirForce, estd. as a separate branch 70 years ago today. Thank you to all the brave airmen keeping us safe. #AFBDay
On this day 230 years ago, our founders adopted the Constitution - a triumph for liberty that laid the groundwork for American greatness.
Appointing a fmr DeVry dean to police for-profit college fraud at @usedgov makes as much sense as trusting Dracula to guard the blood bank.
Proposed base closure measure that could threaten SUBASE & CT National Guard is the wrong approach. I stand w/ local leaders in opposition.
At Monday #DACA hearing in CT, I heard harrowing stories of chaos & confusion from DREAMers who trusted America to keep its promise to them.
I’ll be talking with my constituents across Connecticut about #MedicareForAll – and I challenge my GOP colleagues to do the same.
Women in America have been denied care for too long because of Hyde Amendment restrictions. With #MedicareForAll, Hyde is history.
At a time when the Trump admin seems intent on dismantling reproductive rights, #MedicareForAll would protect women's health.
For those battling addiction, healthcare access is life and death. #MedicareForAll puts crucial treatment and support services in reach.
Every American should be able to access healthcare, regardless of where they live or what they make. That's what #MedicareForAll is about.
It’s time all Americans find the peace of mind seniors have enjoyed for decades. It’s time we pass #MedicareForAll.
My constituents are right. We must lower costs, expand coverage, and protect patients. With #MedicareForAll, we make progress on all three.
